'''Jeh''' (also spelled ''Die, Gie, Yaeh'') is a language spoken by more than fifteen thousand people in [[Vietnam]].  There are also several thousand speakers in the provinces of [[Xekong Province|Xekong]] and [[Attapu Province|Attapu]] in [[Laos]].

