'''Karekin Deveciyan''' (1868 in [[Harput]] &ndash; 1964 in [[Istanbul]]) was a [[Armenians in Turkey|Turkish-Armenian]] [[zoology|zoologist]] who wrote ''Türkiye'de Balık ve Balıkçılık'', one of the first scientific studies on fish and fisheries in Turkey. He served in the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] bureaucracy and hold offices related to fishery.<ref name="acta">{{cite journal |last = Sarıkaya |first = Makbule |date = January 2009 |title = Karekin Deveciyan'ın 1915 Tarihli "Balık ve Balıkçılık" Eseri |url = http://www.actaturcica.com/sayi1/282_294.pdf |journal = Acta Turcica |volume = 1 |issue = 1 |accessdate = 9 February 2014 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140222013032/http://www.actaturcica.com/sayi1/282_294.pdf |archive-date = 2014-02-22 |dead-url = yes |df = }}</ref> He was the grandfather of [[France|French]] politician [[Patrick Devedjian]].<ref name="acta" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.aksam.com.tr/haber.asp?a=54990,5&tarih=08.10.2006 |accessdate=2008-12-06 |title=Ermeni vekil yasaya karşı |section=Dünya |work=Akşam Gazetesi |date=2006-08-10 |language=Turkish }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}} </ref>
