{{Infobox language |name=Khaonh |states=[[Cambodia]] |speakers=375 |date=2016 |ref=<ref>Ethnologue (21st edition)</ref> |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Bahnaric languages|Bahnaric]] |fam3=Central |fam4=South |iso3=hkn |iso3comment=(Mel-Khaonh) |glotto=none }}
'''Khaonh''' is a [[Bahnaric languages|Bahnaric]] language of northeastern Cambodia. It is closely related to [[Mel language|Mel]].
[[Kraol language|Kraol]], [[Thmon language|Thmon]], Khaonh, and [[Mel language|Mel]] all have about 70% lexical similarity with [[Stieng language|Stieng]], a Southern Bahnaric language (Barr & Pawley 2013:32).
Khaonh is spoken in the following villages of [[Kratié Province]], Cambodia (Barr & Pawley 2013). *Chhok, Thmei commune, [[Kratié District]] *Khnach, Thmei commune, [[Kratié District]] *Kosang, Changkrang commune, [[Kratié District]]
==Further reading== http://www-01.sil.org/iso639-3/chg_detail.asp?id=2016-008&lang=hkn
==References== {{Reflist}} *Barr, Julie and Eric Pawley. 2013. ''[http://www.sil.org/resources/publications/entry/52517 Bahnaric Language Cluster survey of Mondul Kiri and Kratie Provinces, Cambodia]''. SIL International.
