{{Infobox language |name = Komodo |region =[[Komodo Island]] and mainland [[Flores]] |state=[[Indonesia]] |ethnicity = [[Komodo people|Komodo]], [[Bugis]], [[Bima people|Bima]] |speakers = 700 |date= 2000 |ref=<!--don't update to e18 w/o date-->e17 |familycolor = Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Central–Eastern Malayo-Polynesian languages|Central–Eastern MP]] |fam4=[[Bima–Sumba languages|Bima–Sumba]] |fam5= |script = [[Latin script|Latin]] |lc1=kvh|ld1=Komodo |glotto=komo1261 |glottoname=Komodo }}
The '''Komodo language''' is a language spoken by the extinct<ref>[http://sains.kompas.com/read/2013/01/28/15514880/penduduk.hidup.bersama.komodo Penduduk Hidup Bersama Komodo]</ref> [[Komodo people]], and present day inhabitants of [[Komodo Island]], with a small population of speakers on mainland [[Flores]].<ref>[http://www.joshuaproject.net/languages.php?rol3=kvh Komodo Speaking Peoples - Joshua Project]</ref> It belongs to the [[Austronesian]] language family, and is a separate language from [[Manggarai language|Manggarai]].
