{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}
'''Naresh Chander Chaturvedi''' (born 30 April 1928) is a writer and poet, predominantly writing in [[Hindi language]]. He was born in [[Farrukhabad]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]. He completed his [[Master of Arts|M. A.]] in Hindi from the [[Jabalpur University]].<ref name=Who>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QA1V7sICaIwC&pg=PA234&lpg=PA234&dq=Naresh+Chandra+Chaturvedi&source=bl&ots=i_ubd5RSJi&sig=beJWgmgEYZMg3ktLU8fsj5W9JlQ&hl=en&sa=X&ei=xuxgU8bTB86FrAfFioD4Bw&ved=0CDEQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=Naresh%20Chandra%20Chaturvedi&f=false | title=Who's who of Indian Writers, 1999: A-M | publisher=[[Sahitya Akademi]] | year=1999 | pages=234 | isbn=8126008733 | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref>

Chaturvedi was the member of [[Indian National Congress]], and was elected to the [[8th Lok Sabha]] from the [[Kanpur (Lok Sabha constituency)|Kanpur constituency]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/biodata_1_12/2996.htm | title=Members Bioprofile - CHATURVEDI, SHRI NARESH CHANDER | publisher=[[Lok Sabha]] | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> He was the general secretary of [[All India Congress Committee]].<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MWVPURa2hE4C&pg=PA592&dq=Naresh+Chandra+Chaturvedi&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Ae5gU5iSKsOjugSTmYL4Bg&ved=0CC4Q6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=Naresh%20Chandra%20Chaturvedi&f=false | title=Twenty Tumultuous Years |author1=Ayub Syed |author2=Anees Jahan Syed |author3=Shri Prakash | pages=592 | isbn=8121208041}}</ref>{{when|date=April 2014}} In 1999, he was the member of [[National Commission for Scheduled Castes|National Commission for SC and ST]].<ref name=Who/>

