'''North American Conference on Afroasiatic Linguistics''' (NACAL) is a yearly academic conference addressing the [[Afroasiatic languages]]. The conference has been held since 1973. Prominent participants have included [[Lionel Bender (linguist)|Lionel Bender]], [[Wolf Leslau]], and [[Alan S. Kaye]].

